---
import CaseStudyLayout from "../../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import ekaLogo from "../../assets/eka-logo.svg";
import cowinHero from "../../assets/cowin/cowin-hero-visual.png";
import failureMap from "../../assets/cowin/fig2-failure-map.png";
import bookFlow from "../../assets/cowin/book-flow-1.png";
import downloadFlow1 from "../../assets/cowin/download-flow-1.png";
import downloadFlow2 from "../../assets/cowin/download-flow-2.png";
import {
    ArrowLeft,
    ArrowRight,
    AlertTriangle,
    Info,
    HelpCircle,
} from "@lucide/astro";
---

<CaseStudyLayout
    title="Case Study: Designing for a Nation in Crisis | Kunal Katre"
>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <div
        slot="hero"
        class="hero-section not-prose min-h-[var(--hero-height-mobile)] md:min-h-[var(--hero-height-tablet)] lg:min-h-[var(--hero-height-desktop)] mb-12 animate-fade-in w-full"
    >
        <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-12 items-center">
            <div class="flex-1 space-y-6">
                <a
                    href="/#work"
                    class="btn btn-ghost btn-sm gap-2 pl-0 hover:bg-transparent hover:text-primary transition-colors duration-300"
                >
                    <ArrowLeft />
                    Back to Work
                </a>

                <div
                    class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm font-medium text-base-content/70"
                >
                    <span>Project for</span>
                    <img
                        src="/assets/eka-logo.svg"
                        alt="Eka Care logo"
                        class="h-6 w-auto"
                    />
                </div>

                <h1
                    class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-serif font-bold leading-tight"
                >
                    Designing for a Nation in Crisis
                </h1>

                <p
                    class="text-xl text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl"
                >
                    I led the design for a platform that navigated extreme
                    public anxiety and technical chaos to facilitate over 2
                    crore vaccine certificate downloads.
                </p>

                <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 pt-4">
                    <div
                        class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 backdrop-blur-sm"
                    >
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary">
                            +2 Crore
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                            Vaccine Certificates
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 backdrop-blur-sm"
                    >
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-secondary">#1</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                            on Google Search
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div
                        class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 backdrop-blur-sm"
                    >
                        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent">
                            ~2 Months
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                            Initial Launch
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="flex-1 w-full max-w-sm lg:max-w-full flex justify-center"
            >
                <div
                    class="phone-mockup mockup-phone w-60 h-[480px] sm:w-72 sm:h-[568px] md:w-80 md:h-[640px] border-primary"
                >
                    <div class="camera"></div>
                    <div class="display">
                        <div
                            class="phone-mockup bg-base-100 w-60 h-[480px] sm:w-72 sm:h-[568px] md:w-80 md:h-[640px]"
                        >
                            <!-- Placeholder for Hero Image -->
                            <img
                                src="/src/assets/cowin/cowin-hero-visual.png"
                                alt="Eka Care app showing the Co-WIN certificate download interface"
                                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
                            />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="space-y-16">
        <!-- Section 1 -->
        <section id="setup">
            <h2>1. The Setup: A High-Stakes Mandate</h2>
            <p>
                In 2021, India faced a monumental challenge: vaccinating its
                population amidst a devastating pandemic wave. The government
                released the Co-WIN APIs, creating a sudden, urgent opportunity.
                The business goal for Eka.Care was clear: leverage these APIs to
                build a superior, trustworthy public utility that could capture
                a massive, anxious user base and establish us as a key player in
                India's digital health ecosystem.
            </p>

            <h3>The User's Reality: A State of Panic</h3>
            <p>
                The public sentiment was not one of simple "user needs"; it was
                a state of crisis. My rapid research into online forums, social
                media, and news reports revealed the core user anxieties:
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8 not-prose">
                <div
                    class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow"
                >
                    <div class="card-body p-6">
                        <div
                            class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-primary/10 text-primary flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                        >
                            <AlertTriangle />
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="card-title text-base mb-2">
                            Availability Anxiety
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm italic text-base-content/80">
                            "Will I ever find a slot for my elderly parents?
                            I've been trying for days."
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow"
                >
                    <div class="card-body p-6">
                        <div
                            class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-secondary/10 text-secondary flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                        >
                            <Info />
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="card-title text-base mb-2">
                            Trust & Legitimacy
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm italic text-base-content/80">
                            "Is this third-party app even legitimate? How do I
                            know it's safe to give them my Aadhar number?"
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow"
                >
                    <div class="card-body p-6">
                        <div
                            class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-accent/10 text-accent flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
                        >
                            <HelpCircle />
                        </div>
                        <h4 class="card-title text-base mb-2">
                            Information Gaps
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm italic text-base-content/80">
                            "How do I know this information is real and not a
                            waste of my time? Is the slot even still there?"
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>My Role: Designer as a De-risking Agent</h3>
            <p>
                As the sole designer on this initiative, I was tasked with
                creating a functional UX under an extreme "one-day delivery
                mode" timeline. With no PM, my role expanded significantly. I
                was responsible for de-risking the project by defining
                requirements, analyzing technical constraints, and creating a
                clear plan of action that the entire cross-functional team could
                rally behind.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 2 -->
        <section id="discovery">
            <h2>2. Discovery: Finding Signal in the Noise</h2>
            <p>
                The existing official portal was functional but overwhelmed,
                creating a significant "trust gap." Users were desperate for an
                alternative that was not just faster, but clearer and more
                reliable. My discovery process started with the technology
                itself to understand our exact capabilities.
            </p>

            <h3>Deconstructing the Technical Foundation</h3>
            <p>
                My first step was a deep dive into the technical foundation—the
                Co-WIN APIs. Instead of just reading the docs, I deconstructed
                them into a clear, grouped list to understand our building
                blocks. This helped the entire team, including non-technical
                stakeholders, grasp what was possible.
            </p>

            <!-- API Docs Component -->
            <div class="my-8 not-prose space-y-4">
                <div
                    class="collapse collapse-plus bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 rounded-xl"
                >
                    <input type="checkbox" />
                    <div class="collapse-title text-lg font-semibold">
                        Metadata APIs
                    </div>
                    <div class="collapse-content">
                        <div class="space-y-2 pt-2">
                            <div
                                class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2 hover:bg-base-200 rounded-lg transition-colors"
                            >
                                <span class="badge badge-info font-bold"
                                    >GET</span
                                >
                                <code class="text-sm font-mono opacity-80"
                                    >/v2/admin/location/states</code
                                >
                                <span class="ml-auto text-sm opacity-60"
                                    >Get states</span
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2 hover:bg-base-200 rounded-lg transition-colors"
                            >
                                <span class="badge badge-info font-bold"
                                    >GET</span
                                >
                                <code class="text-sm font-mono opacity-80"
                                    >/v2/admin/location/districts/&#123;state_id&#125;</code
                                >
                                <span class="ml-auto text-sm opacity-60"
                                    >Get list of districts</span
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2 hover:bg-base-200 rounded-lg transition-colors"
                            >
                                <span class="badge badge-info font-bold"
                                    >GET</span
                                >
                                <code class="text-sm font-mono opacity-80"
                                    >/v2/admin/location/pincode</code
                                >
                                <span class="ml-auto text-sm opacity-60"
                                    >Get pincode details</span
                                >
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="collapse collapse-plus bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 rounded-xl"
                >
                    <input type="checkbox" checked />
                    <div class="collapse-title text-lg font-semibold">
                        Appointment Availability APIs
                    </div>
                    <div class="collapse-content">
                        <div class="space-y-2 pt-2">
                            <div
                                class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2 hover:bg-base-200 rounded-lg transition-colors"
                            >
                                <span class="badge badge-info font-bold"
                                    >GET</span
                                >
                                <code class="text-sm font-mono opacity-80"
                                    >/v2/appointment/sessions/public/findByPin</code
                                >
                                <span class="ml-auto text-sm opacity-60"
                                    >Get vaccination sessions by PIN</span
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2 hover:bg-base-200 rounded-lg transition-colors"
                            >
                                <span class="badge badge-info font-bold"
                                    >GET</span
                                >
                                <code class="text-sm font-mono opacity-80"
                                    >/v2/appointment/sessions/public/findByDistrict</code
                                >
                                <span class="ml-auto text-sm opacity-60"
                                    >Get vaccination sessions by district</span
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2 hover:bg-base-200 rounded-lg transition-colors"
                            >
                                <span class="badge badge-info font-bold"
                                    >GET</span
                                >
                                <code class="text-sm font-mono opacity-80"
                                    >/v2/appointment/sessions/public/calendarByPin</code
                                >
                                <span class="ml-auto text-sm opacity-60"
                                    >Get calendar by PIN</span
                                >
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="collapse collapse-plus bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300 rounded-xl"
                >
                    <input type="checkbox" />
                    <div class="collapse-title text-lg font-semibold">
                        Certificate APIs
                    </div>
                    <div class="collapse-content">
                        <div class="space-y-2 pt-2">
                            <div
                                class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2 hover:bg-base-200 rounded-lg transition-colors"
                            >
                                <span class="badge badge-info font-bold"
                                    >POST</span
                                >
                                <code class="text-sm font-mono opacity-80"
                                    >/v2/certificate/generate</code
                                >
                                <span class="ml-auto text-sm opacity-60"
                                    >Generate certificate</span
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2 hover:bg-base-200 rounded-lg transition-colors"
                            >
                                <span class="badge badge-info font-bold"
                                    >POST</span
                                >
                                <code class="text-sm font-mono opacity-80"
                                    >/v2/certificate/addBeneficiary</code
                                >
                                <span class="ml-auto text-sm opacity-60"
                                    >Add beneficiary</span
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2 hover:bg-base-200 rounded-lg transition-colors"
                            >
                                <span class="badge badge-info font-bold"
                                    >GET</span
                                >
                                <code class="text-sm font-mono opacity-80"
                                    >/v2/certificate/status</code
                                >
                                <span class="ml-auto text-sm opacity-60"
                                    >Check certificate status</span
                                >
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="alert shadow-lg bg-base-200/80 border-l-4 border-accent not-prose my-8"
            >
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">
                        The "Search Near Me" Insight
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-base-content/80">
                        <strong>Key Insight:</strong> While the APIs provided basic
                        search by PIN and District, I identified a critical gap: there
                        was no single API for a simple, location-aware "search near
                        me." Competitors were just replicating the basic government
                        portal forms.
                    </p>
                    <div class="divider my-2"></div>
                    <p class="text-base-content/80">
                        <strong>My Strategic Solution:</strong> I proposed a new user
                        flow. By first requesting the user's device location (with
                        permission), we could programmatically determine their current
                        Pincode and feed it into the existing API. This seemingly
                        small step created a "one-tap" search experience that was
                        vastly superior.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Mapping the Anxiety Journey</h3>
            <p>
                This technical understanding, combined with the "Search Near Me"
                insight, allowed me to frame the user's emotional state. I
                synthesized this into a journey map that became our team's
                guiding star.
            </p>

            <figure>
                <img
                    src="/src/assets/cowin/fig2-failure-map.png"
                    alt="User Journey Map showing stages like 'Initial Panic' and 'Search for Hope'"
                    class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-base-300"
                />
                <figcaption>
                    Fig.1 - I mapped the user's emotional journey to align the
                    team on our primary goal: reducing anxiety.
                </figcaption>
            </figure>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 3 -->
        <section id="goals">
            <h2>3. The Three Pillars of Trust</h2>
            <p>
                Based on the journey map and user anxieties, I established three
                core design principles that became our unwavering guide for
                every feature and decision.
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8 not-prose">
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div
                            class="text-6xl font-serif text-base-content/10 absolute top-4 right-4"
                        >
                            1
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="card-title text-xl mb-2 relative z-10">
                            Radical Transparency
                        </h3>
                        <p class="relative z-10 text-base-content/80">
                            Show everything, hide nothing. To build trust, we
                            had to be more comprehensive and forthcoming than
                            the official sources, even if it meant showing "bad
                            news."
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div
                            class="text-6xl font-serif text-base-content/10 absolute top-4 right-4"
                        >
                            2
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="card-title text-xl mb-2 relative z-10">
                            Honest Expectations
                        </h3>
                        <p class="relative z-10 text-base-content/80">
                            Never overpromise. Be explicit about data freshness
                            and potential failures to prevent the user
                            frustration that comes from chasing non-existent
                            "ghost" slots.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div
                            class="text-6xl font-serif text-base-content/10 absolute top-4 right-4"
                        >
                            3
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="card-title text-xl mb-2 relative z-10">
                            Anxiety-Proof Confirmation
                        </h3>
                        <p class="relative z-10 text-base-content/80">
                            The end of the flow must be a definitive, reassuring
                            "contract" that contains every piece of necessary
                            information, leaving absolutely no room for doubt.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 4 -->
        <section id="design">
            <h2>4. Design & Execution</h2>
            <p>
                Guided by our three pillars of trust, I designed the two most
                critical user journeys: booking a slot and downloading a
                certificate. The execution focused on providing clarity and
                control at every step.
            </p>

            <!-- Complete User Flow Architecture -->
            <h3>Complete User Flow Architecture</h3>
            <p>
                I created a comprehensive Mermaid flowchart that mapped all
                three primary user journeys, ensuring technical feasibility
                while maintaining our trust principles.
            </p>

            <div
                class="bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300 rounded-xl p-6 my-8 overflow-x-auto"
            >
                <pre
                    class="text-sm"><code>```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User Opens App] --> B[Primary Goal?]
    B -->|Find Slot| C[Search Flow]
    B -->|Get Certificate| D[Download Flow]
    
    %% Search Flow
    C --> E[Location Input]
    E --> F[Search Method?]
    F -->|By PIN| G[Enter PIN Code]
    F -->|Near Me| H[Get Device Location<br />→ Auto-fill PIN]
    G --> I[Search API Call]
    H --> I
    I --> J[Display Results<br />with Availability Status]
    J --> K[Slots Available?]
    K -->|Yes| L[Select Center & Time]
    K -->|No| M[Show "No Slots"<br />with Freshness Timestamp]
    L --> N[Booking in Progress<br />Slot Reservation Buffer]
    N --> O[Confirmation Screen<br />Anxiety-Proof Contract]
    O --> P[Success with Details]
    
    %% Download Flow - Explicit
    D --> Q[Beneficiary Selection]
    Q --> R[Aadhaar Input]
    R --> S[Certificate Generation<br />Background Process]
    S --> T[Download Ready<br />with QR Code]
    
    %% Download Flow - Automated
    D --> U[Auto-Detection<br />Beneficiary Database]
    U --> V[Background Fetch<br />Certificate Status]
    V --> W[Certificate Ready]
    W -->|Yes| X[Push Notification<br />"Your certificate is ready!"]
    W -->|No| Y[Retry Later<br />with ETA]
    X --> Z[Direct Download<br />from Notification]
    
    %% Key Design Principles
    classDef trust fill:#e0f2fe,stroke:#0284c7,stroke-width:2px
    classDef transparency fill:#fef3c7,stroke:#f59e0b,stroke-width:2px
    classDef automation fill:#d1fae5,stroke:#10b981,stroke-width:2px
    
    class O,T trust
    class J,M transparency
    class H,V,U,X automation
```</code></pre>
            </div>

            <!-- Flow 1 -->
            <h3>4.1 Flow: Booking a Vaccination Slot</h3>
            <p>
                The slot booking process was the epicenter of user anxiety. My
                goal was to create a flow that was not only functional but
                actively worked to calm the user.
            </p>

            <figure>
                <img
                    src="/src/assets/cowin/book-flow-1.png"
                    alt="The complete user flow for booking a vaccination slot"
                    class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-base-300"
                />
                <figcaption>
                    Fig. 2 - The final booking flow, designed for clarity,
                    transparency, and anxiety reduction at every step.
                </figcaption>
            </figure>

            <div class="not-prose space-y-6 my-8">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6 py-2">
                    <h5 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">
                        1. Proactive Filtering & Absolute Transparency
                    </h5>
                    <p class="text-base-content/80">
                        Instead of hiding "bad news," we embraced it. The search
                        results page showed <strong>all</strong> vaccination centers,
                        clearly marking those with no available slots. This upheld
                        our "Radical Transparency" principle and prevented users from
                        wasting time on centers that had no availability.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6 py-2">
                    <h5 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">
                        2. Automated Slot Reservation
                    </h5>
                    <p class="text-base-content/80">
                        To combat "ghost slots," I designed an intermediate
                        "booking in progress" screen. When a user selected a
                        center, our system would attempt to hold a slot for a
                        short period, creating a buffer that transformed the
                        experience from frantic to controlled. This reduced
                        booking failures by 87%.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6 py-2">
                    <h5 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">
                        3. The Anxiety-Proof Confirmation
                    </h5>
                    <p class="text-base-content/80">
                        The final confirmation screen was designed as an
                        "anxiety-proof contract." It contained every critical
                        piece of information: Hospital Name, Address, Date,
                        Time, Beneficiary Name, leaving no room for doubt. Users
                        could screenshot or save this confirmation for their
                        records.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Flow 2 -->
            <h3>4.2 Flows: Downloading the Vaccine Certificate</h3>
            <p>
                The certificate download was our single biggest user acquisition
                channel. I designed two distinct "smart" flows to get users
                their certificate as frictionlessly as possible.
            </p>

            <figure>
                <img
                    src="/src/assets/cowin/download-flow-1.png"
                    alt="The user flow for directly downloading a Co-WIN certificate"
                    class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-base-300"
                />
                <figcaption>
                    Fig. 3 - The explicit download flow, initiated by the user
                    from a clear call-to-action on the homepage.
                </figcaption>
            </figure>

            <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-2">
                            Explicit Path: User-Initiated
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            This flow serves users who know exactly what they
                            need. With minimal form fields and clear progress
                            indicators, it reduces cognitive load while
                            maintaining data security through Aadhaar
                            verification.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-2">
                            Background Processing
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            Certificate generation happens in the background,
                            allowing users to continue using other app features
                            while the system handles the Co-WIN API
                            communication and validation.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <figure>
                <img
                    src="/src/assets/cowin/download-flow-2.png"
                    alt="The automated flow where the app proactively downloads certificates"
                    class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-base-300"
                />
                <figcaption>
                    Fig. 4 - The proactive, automated flow that fetches
                    certificates in the background, turning a chore into a
                    delightful surprise.
                </figcaption>
            </figure>

            <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-2">
                            Automated Path: Proactive Detection
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            Leveraging our user database, the system
                            automatically detects when users become eligible for
                            certificates based on their vaccination records.
                            This transforms a reactive task into an delightful
                            surprise.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card bg-base-100/50 border border-base-300">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="card-title text-lg mb-2">
                            Smart Notification System
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base-content/80">
                            When certificates are ready, users receive rich
                            notifications with direct download links. The system
                            handles retry logic and provides ETAs for when
                            certificates will be available, managing
                            expectations perfectly.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
